						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Do you know what settings you use for electric guitar sounds?</div><br /><br />Usually a square wave on the carrier, and a sine wave (usually one octave down, although sometimes I fool around to limited effect) on the modulator (if I'm using the terminology right). Psuedo-feedback effects can be achieved by simply dialing the modulator's gain (gradually) to zero.<br /><br />I also have used two square waves, although I usually prefer them at the same frequency.</div>

